<div id="review_2555388916" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2555388916" />
    <a title="Tan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12812571-tan"><img alt="Tan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1371014129p2/12812571.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2555388916?book_show_action=true">Oct 12, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tan" href="/user/show/12812571-tan">Tan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12812571-tan?shelf=rpabookclub">rpabookclub</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer2555388916&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2555388916" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4121313606731155753">You know what, I expected to dislike it more. <br/><br/>The beginning frustrated me because I couldn&apos;t stand the characters and the way they behaved, but as the story went on, I sympathised and was caught up in their story. I wanted to skip over all of Nelson&apos;s parts though - I felt he was a terrible person, incredibly manipulative and kind of just existed to be a cautionary AIDS tale? It read as if Sanchez wanted the reader to feel sorry for Nelson, but, sorry, he&apos;s a crappy friend and person who doesn&apos;t</span>
  <span id="freeText4121313606731155753" style="display:none">You know what, I expected to dislike it more. <br /><br />The beginning frustrated me because I couldn't stand the characters and the way they behaved, but as the story went on, I sympathised and was caught up in their story. I wanted to skip over all of Nelson's parts though - I felt he was a terrible person, incredibly manipulative and kind of just existed to be a cautionary AIDS tale? It read as if Sanchez wanted the reader to feel sorry for Nelson, but, sorry, he's a crappy friend and person who doesn't take responsibility for his actions, so why should we?<br /><br />The plot was okay, like I said, I got caught up in the lives of the boys (especially Jason's home life, and Kyle's coming out to his parents), but the writing was quite amateurish. There was a lot of telling rather than showing. It was just alright. Could have been better. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4121313606731155753" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review2555388916">
  <td colspan="2">
    <div class="updateActionLinks">
        <a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link2555388916" title="Flag this review as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=2555388916&amp;resource_type=Review&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F94064.Rainbow_Boys">flag</a>





      <span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_review_2555388916'><a id="like_count_review_2555388916" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/2555388916?resource_type=Review"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it gr-button gr-button--small" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F94064.Rainbow_Boys">Like</a></span>
&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a href="/review/show/2555388916?book_show_action=true&amp;from_review_page=1">see review</a>
    </div>


    <div id='comments_for_review_2555388916' style='display: none;'>
