<span id="freeTextContainer4167220355644555810">The book is told through 3 boys eyes with alternating chapters of each of their perspectives. <b>Kyle</b>, a nice boy, whose a swimmer. He hangs out with <b>Nelson</b> a gay boy who&apos;s obviously gay. Also, Kyle is in love with <b>Jason</b>, a basketball player. Through the course of the book Kyle comes out to his parents. So does Jason and they become boyfriends? There relationship is kind of not official at the end of the book. They definitely like each other though. Kyle and Nelson have to deal with violence from a</span>
  <span id="freeText4167220355644555810" style="display:none">The book is told through 3 boys eyes with alternating chapters of each of their perspectives. <b>Kyle</b>, a nice boy, whose a swimmer. He hangs out with <b>Nelson</b> a gay boy who's obviously gay. Also, Kyle is in love with <b>Jason</b>, a basketball player. Through the course of the book Kyle comes out to his parents. So does Jason and they become boyfriends? There relationship is kind of not official at the end of the book. They definitely like each other though. Kyle and Nelson have to deal with violence from a couple of other boys at school. They get picked on, threatened, and prank called. In one fight, Jason defends them. The book is simply written and enjoyable. Not the best YA I've read but one of the very few that deals with gay boys as the protaganists.</span>
